author: Reuters Editorial
title: Moscow says it will not comply with U.S. sanctions on Venezuela's state debt: Interfax
text:
May 22, 2018 / 4:10 PM / in a few seconds Moscow says it will not comply with U.S. sanctions on Venezuela's state debt: Interfax Reuters Staff 1 Min Read
MOSCOW (Reuters) - Moscow has a negative view of U.S. sanctions against Venezuela’s state debt and will not comply with them, Alexander Shchetinin, the head of Latin American department at Russia’s Foreign Ministry, was quoted as saying by Interfax news agency on Tuesday.
Venezuela on Monday said new U.S. sanctions restricting its ability to liquidate state assets and debt in the United States were “illegal measures”. Reporting by Polina Devitt; Editing by Kevin Liffey
